<subSubSection id="598F44A4CE79FFC1FF31CE125BF655D3" pageId="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="112A172FCE79FFC1FF31CE1258015757" blockId="4.[132,1237,825,1786]" pageId="4">
The 
<taxonomicName id="D6956CACCE79FFC1FF6DCE115B7F507A" authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1950" box="[232,351,826,851]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Trigonisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="23E1CB3DCE79FFC1FF6DCE115B7F507A" box="[232,351,826,851]" italics="true" pageId="4">Trigonisca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus group clade, comprising the extant genus 
<taxonomicName id="D6956CACCE79FFC1FC26CE115E3A507A" authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1950" box="[931,1050,826,851]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Trigonisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="23E1CB3DCE79FFC1FC26CE115E3A507A" box="[931,1050,826,851]" italics="true" pageId="4">Trigonisca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the extinct genus 
<taxonomicName id="D6956CACCE79FFC1FF4BCE745B475050" authorityName="Engel &amp; Michener" authorityYear="2013" box="[206,359,863,889]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Exebotrigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="23E1CB3DCE79FFC1FF4BCE745B475050" box="[206,359,863,889]" italics="true" pageId="4">Exebotrigona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is united by the combination of a minute body size, with a length typically 
<quantity id="D66DBACACE79FFC1FF01CEAF5AFF50B6" box="[132,223,900,927]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="4" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
or frequently less, and a forewing length of 
<quantity id="D66DBACACE79FFC1FD6FCEAF591050B6" box="[746,816,900,927]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="4" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
or less; a distinctly broadened base to the marginal cell, with a basal angle (angle formed within the marginal cell between pterostigmal margin and r-rs) of 68°–90°, and the marginal cell, at tangent of pterostigmal apex, broader than submarginal cell area; the posterior margin of the metatibia nodulose or tuberculate, sometimes weakly so (apparently not nodulose in 
<taxonomicName id="D6956CACCE79FFC1FCE6C93259DC571A" authorityName="Engel &amp; Michener" authorityYear="2013" box="[867,1020,1049,1075]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Exebotrigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="23E1CB3DCE79FFC1FCE6C93259DC571A" box="[867,1020,1049,1075]" italics="true" pageId="4">Exebotrigona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), owing to prominent bristle bases; and the setae of the inner surface of the metabasitarsus arranged in transverse rows (
<bibRefCitation id="75046ADECE79FFC1FE95C94F5BEB5757" author="Michener" box="[272,459,1124,1150]" firstAuthor="Michener" pageId="4" pagination="75 - 163" refId="ref13162" refString="Michener, C. D. 1990. Classification of the Apidae (Hymenoptera). University of Kansas Science Bulletin 54 (4): 75 - 163." type="journal article" year="1990">Michener, 1990</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="75046ADECE79FFC1FE52C94F58345757" author="Michener" box="[471,532,1124,1150]" firstAuthor="Michener" pageId="4" refId="ref13232" refString="Michener, C. D. 2007. The bees of the world, 2 nd ed. Baltimore: Johns Hopkins University Press, xvi + [i] + 953 pp., + 20 pls." type="book" year="2007">2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="112A172FCE79FFC1FF31C9A25BF655D3" blockId="4.[132,1237,825,1786]" pageId="4">
Presently, there are 45 species contained in the 
<taxonomicName id="D6956CACCE79FFC1FC84C9A1595F578A" authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1950" box="[769,895,1162,1187]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Trigonisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="23E1CB3DCE79FFC1FC84C9A1595F578A" box="[769,895,1162,1187]" italics="true" pageId="4">Trigonisca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus group, including the species described herein, and these are arranged into four subgenera, which are sometimes treated as distinct genera (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="75046ADECE79FFC1FDD4C9FE58D257C6" author="Moure" box="[593,754,1236,1263]" firstAuthor="Moure" pageId="4" pagination="241 - 260" refId="ref13271" refString="Moure, J. S. 1950. Contribuicao para o conhecimento das especies brasileiras de Hypotrigona Cockerell (Hymen. - Apoidea). Dusenia 1 (4): 241 - 260." type="journal article" year="1950">Moure, 1950</bibRefCitation>
). The analysis of 
<bibRefCitation id="75046ADECE79FFC1FC4DC9FE5B3C563D" author="Rasmussen and Cameron" firstAuthor="Rasmussen" pageId="4" pagination="206 - 232" refId="ref13790" refString="Rasmussen, C., and S. A. Cameron. 2010. Global stingless bee phylogeny supports ancient divergence, vicariance, and long distance dispersal. Biological Journal of the Linnean Society 99 (1): 206 - 232." type="journal article" year="2010">Rasmussen and Cameron (2010)</bibRefCitation>
indicated the likelihood that 
<taxonomicName id="D6956CACCE79FFC1FD28C9D1596E563A" authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1950" box="[685,846,1274,1299]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Leurotrigona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="lato">
<emphasis id="23E1CB3DCE79FFC1FD28C9D1596E563A" box="[685,846,1274,1299]" italics="true" pageId="4">Leurotrigona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="38D27646CE79FFC1FCDEC9D2595D563A" box="[859,893,1273,1299]" pageId="4" sensu="lato">s.l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is paraphyletic, and so is treated as two distinct groups herein. 
<taxonomicName id="D6956CACCE79FFC1FDE6C80B59215610" authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1950" box="[611,769,1312,1337]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Leurotrigona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="23E1CB3DCE79FFC1FDE6C80B59215610" box="[611,769,1312,1337]" italics="true" pageId="4">Leurotrigona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="38D27646CE79FFC1FC8EC83459645610" box="[779,836,1311,1337]" pageId="4" sensu="stricto">s.str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D6956CACCE79FFC1FC00C8345E165610" authority="Engel &amp; Rozen &amp; Sepúlveda-Cano &amp; Smith &amp; Thomas &amp; Ospina-Torres &amp; Gonzalez, 2019" authorityName="Engel &amp; Rozen &amp; Sepúlveda-Cano &amp; Smith &amp; Thomas &amp; Ospina-Torres &amp; Gonzalez" authorityYear="2019" box="[901,1078,1311,1337]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Trigonisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="new subgenus" subGenus="Exochotrigona">
<emphasis id="23E1CB3DCE79FFC1FC00C8345E165610" box="[901,1078,1311,1337]" italics="true" pageId="4">Exochotrigona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="38D27646CE79FFC1FBC2C8345A925676" pageId="4" rank="subGenus">new subgenus</taxonomicNameLabel>
, each with two species (
<bibRefCitation id="75046ADECE79FFC1FE65C86F590A5677" author="Pedro and Camargo" box="[480,810,1348,1374]" firstAuthor="Pedro" pageId="4" pagination="37 - 54" refId="ref12574" refString="Camargo, J. M. F., and S. R. M. Pedro. 2009. Neotropical Meliponini: the genus Celetrigona Moure (Hymenoptera: Apidae, Apinae). Zootaxa 2155: 37 - 54." type="journal article" year="2009">Pedro and Camargo, 2009</bibRefCitation>
; see below), while 
<taxonomicName id="D6956CACCE79FFC1FB93C86F5E825677" authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1950" box="[1046,1186,1348,1374]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Celetrigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="23E1CB3DCE79FFC1FB93C86F5E825677" box="[1046,1186,1348,1374]" italics="true" pageId="4">Celetrigona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has four species (
<bibRefCitation id="75046ADECE79FFC1FEA8C841585A56AD" author="Camargo and Pedro" box="[301,634,1385,1412]" firstAuthor="Camargo" pageId="4" pagination="37 - 54" refId="ref12574" refString="Camargo, J. M. F., and S. R. M. Pedro. 2009. Neotropical Meliponini: the genus Celetrigona Moure (Hymenoptera: Apidae, Apinae). Zootaxa 2155: 37 - 54." type="journal article" year="2009">Camargo and Pedro, 2009</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="D6956CACCE79FFC1FD40C841596356AA" authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1950" box="[709,835,1386,1411]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Trigonisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="23E1CB3DCE79FFC1FD40C841596356AA" box="[709,835,1386,1411]" italics="true" pageId="4">Trigonisca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="38D27646CE79FFC1FCC8C84159A656AD" box="[845,902,1386,1412]" pageId="4" sensu="stricto">s.str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="D6956CACCE79FFC1FC32C8425EEB56AD" authority="Moure" authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1950" box="[951,1227,1385,1412]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Dolichotrigona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="23E1CB3DCE79FFC1FC32C8425E4D56AA" box="[951,1133,1385,1411]" italics="true" pageId="4">Dolichotrigona</emphasis>
Moure
</taxonomicName>
) has 37 (Albuquerque, 1990; Ayala, 1999; Albuquerque and Camargo, 2007; 
<bibRefCitation id="75046ADECE79FFC1FBA8C8A45B3D56E6" author="Camargo and Pedro" firstAuthor="Camargo" pageId="4" pagination="69 - 92" refId="ref12526" refString="Camargo, J. M. F., and S. R. M. Pedro. 2005. Meliponini neotropicais: o genero Dolichotrigona Moure (Hymenoptera, Apidae, Apinae). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia 49 (1): 69 - 92." type="journal article" year="2005">Camargo and Pedro, 2005</bibRefCitation>
; Alvarez and Lucia, 2018; herein). Five species of the group are currently recorded as occurring within 
<collectingCountry id="698257BFCE79FFC1FD84C8F1585E56DD" box="[513,638,1498,1524]" name="Colombia" pageId="4">Colombia</collectingCountry>
: 
<taxonomicName id="D6956CACCE79FFC1FD08C8F15AD75530" authority="Pedro and Camargo" authorityName="Pedro and Camargo" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Trigonisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crispula" subGenus="Exochotrigona">
<emphasis id="23E1CB3DCE79FFC1FD08C8F1592B56DA" box="[653,779,1498,1523]" italics="true" pageId="4">Trigonisca</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="23E1CB3DCE79FFC1FCA4C8F159F256DD" box="[801,978,1498,1524]" italics="true" pageId="4">Exochotrigona</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="23E1CB3DCE79FFC1FC62C8F15E6856DD" box="[999,1096,1498,1524]" italics="true" pageId="4">crispula</emphasis>
Pedro and Camargo
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D6956CACCE79FFC1FE81CB2B58E05533" authority="(Friese)" baseAuthorityName="Friese" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[260,704,1535,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Trigonisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicornis" subGenus="Celetrigona">
<emphasis id="23E1CB3DCE79FFC1FE81CB2B5B365530" box="[260,278,1536,1561]" italics="true" pageId="4">T</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="23E1CB3DCE79FFC1FEB4C8D45B9D5530" box="[305,445,1535,1561]" italics="true" pageId="4">Celetrigona</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="23E1CB3DCE79FFC1FE55C8D458755530" box="[464,597,1535,1561]" italics="true" pageId="4">longicornis</emphasis>
(Friese)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D6956CACCE79FFC1FD48CB2B5E575533" authority="(Friese)" baseAuthorityName="Friese" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[717,1143,1535,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Trigonisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schulthessi" subGenus="Trigonisca">
<emphasis id="23E1CB3DCE79FFC1FD48CB2B58FF5530" box="[717,735,1536,1561]" italics="true" pageId="4">T</emphasis>
. (
